  {
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Hm, I don't know about the internals of InstantSearch and when results are arriving, but can we detect that there is no main index present?\r\nIn that case, `results` will always be `null` (and has always been), and it makes sense to update `scopedResults` directly.",
    "created_at": "2024-04-16T06:47:41Z",
    "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/6132#issuecomment-2058356353",
